strongs_words dataset — license & attribution
=============================================

This DATA is released under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0
International (CC BY-SA 4.0): https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

It is a derived dataset. You must attribute the upstream sources and keep
share-alike derivatives under a compatible license. Each data file also records
its own `source` / `license` in a `#` header line.

Sources
-------
- Aligned surfaces (surfaces/, surfaces_by_method/, attestations/):
  derived from Clear-Bible/Alignments (https://github.com/Clear-Bible/Alignments),
  original-language texts SBLGNT and WLC-Macula. Per-source licenses apply.
- Glosses (glosses/):
  * method=lexicon, source=ubs-dict — UBS Hebrew/Greek dictionaries via
    BibleAquifer (https://github.com/BibleAquifer), CC BY-SA 4.0.
  * method=lexicon, source=stepbible — STEPBible-Data
    (https://github.com/STEPBible/STEPBible-Data), CC BY 4.0.
  * method=llm, source=inhouse-llm — generated for the bcv-query project,
    anchored on the original-language lemma.

Suggested attribution
---------------------
"strongs_words (bcv-query), CC BY-SA 4.0, derived from Clear-Bible/Alignments,
UBS dictionaries (via BibleAquifer), and STEPBible-Data."

The code that produces this dataset (bcv-query) is separately licensed MIT.
